        <p>Context-sensitive Help (CSH) is a way to tie your existing topics with specific dialogs or windows in a software application, or with simple web links created somewhere (e.g., on a website). When users open a particular dialog or window in a software application, or click a web link, they can quickly open a topic pertaining to it.</p>
